<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This should be migrated to a constexpr function when our minimum</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// compiler support is enough for multi-statement constexpr functions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> T&gt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements">CalculateSmallVectorDefaultInlinedElements</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Parameter controlling the default number of inlined elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for &#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The default number of inlined elements ensures that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 There is at least one inlined element.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 &#96;sizeof(SmallVector&lt;T&gt;) &lt;= kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof&#96; unless</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// it contradicts 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e">kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof</a> = 64;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// static&#95;assert that sizeof(T) is not &quot;too big&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1140"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Because our policy guarantees at least one inlined element, it is possible</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for an arbitrarily large inlined element to allocate an arbitrarily large</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// amount of inline storage. We generally consider it an antipattern for a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1144"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SmallVector to allocate an excessive amount of inline storage, so we want</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1145"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to call attention to these cases and make sure that users are making an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1146"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intentional decision if they request a lot of inline storage.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1147"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1148"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We want this assertion to trigger in pathological cases, but otherwise</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1149"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not be too easy to hit. To accomplish that, the cutoff is actually somewhat</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1150"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// larger than kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof (otherwise,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1151"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#96;SmallVector&lt;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&gt;&#96; would be one easy way to trip it, and that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1152"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pattern seems useful in practice).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1153"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1154"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// One wrinkle is that this assertion is in theory non-portable, since</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1155"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sizeof(T) is in general platform-dependent. However, we don&#39;t expect this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1156"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to be much of an issue, because most LLVM development happens on 64-bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1157"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// hosts, and therefore sizeof(T) is expected to &#42;decrease&#42; when compiled for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1158"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 32-bit hosts, dodging the issue. The reverse situation, where development</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1159"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// happens on a 32-bit host and then fails due to sizeof(T) &#42;increasing&#42; on a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1160"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 64-bit host, is expected to be very rare.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1161"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static&#95;assert</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1162"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>) &lt;= 256,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1163"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;You are trying to use a default number of inlined elements for &quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1164"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;&#96;SmallVector&lt;T&gt;&#96; but &#96;sizeof(T)&#96; is really big! Please use an &quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1165"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;explicit number of inlined elements with &#96;SmallVector&lt;T, N&gt;&#96; to make &quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1166"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;sure you really want that much inline storage.&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1167"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1168"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Discount the size of the header itself when calculating the maximum inline</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1169"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bytes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1170" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290">PreferredInlineBytes</a> =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1171"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a322876b665b12084a3401951797b440e">kPreferredSmallVectorSizeof</a> - </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;T, 0&gt;</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1172" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a> = <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#adebf52e29c244776b4747cb57ec94290">PreferredInlineBytes</a> / </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1173" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017">value</a> =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1174"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a> == 0 ? 1 : <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#add4da5518b19db6e0bdf69e7972cb7e3">NumElementsThatFit</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1175"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1176"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This is a &#39;vector&#39; (really, a variable-sized array), optimized</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// for the case when the array is small.  It contains some number of elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1179"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// in-place, which allows it to avoid heap allocation when the actual number of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// elements is below that threshold.  This allows normal &quot;small&quot; cases to be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1181"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// fast without losing generality for large inputs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\note</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1184"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// In the absence of a well-motivated choice for the number of inlined</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1185"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// elements \\p N, it is recommended to use \\c SmallVector&lt;T&gt; (that is,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1186"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// omitting the \\p N). This will choose a default number of inlined elements</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1187"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// reasonable for allocation on the stack (for example, trying to keep \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1188"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// sizeof(SmallVector&lt;T&gt;) around 64 bytes).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1189"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1190"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\warning This does not attempt to be exception safe.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1191"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1192"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\see https://llvm.org/docs/ProgrammersManual.html#llvm-adt-smallvector-h</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1193"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/mips/mips16isellowering-cpp/#a0acb682b8260ab1c60b918599864e2e5">T</a>,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1194"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a> = <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/calculatesmallvectordefaultinlinedelements/#a737320006b419bc7865600d50e558017">CalculateSmallVectorDefaultInlinedElements&lt;T&gt;::value</a>&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1195" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a61e566d072949de225fa6912528beaf5">LLVM&#95;GSL&#95;OWNER</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector/#a3c60758d71502ce394548f12077937ea">SmallVector</a> : </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl/#abd001dbc8a624eecaa020c6d4e3a6b06">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt;T&gt;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1196"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                   <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/smallvectorstorage">SmallVectorStorage</a>&lt;T, N&gt; &#123;</span></CodeLine>
